| A | $23\text{ g/kg}$ | $31\text{ g/kg}$ |
| B | $16\text{ g/kg}$ | $12\text{ g/kg}$ |', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"At deep depth, A recorded $31\\text{ g/kg}$ versus B''s $12\\text{ g/kg}$. Read from the wrong row, this cites deep-depth values to judge a shallow-depth claim and misverifies the inversion —against the impression the opening invites, in the passage''s own terms, as the argument is staged, given the stated qualifiers.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Data Misread] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."},{"id":"B","text":"Across the shallow row, the two methods differ by $7\\text{ g/kg}$. This is an accurate shallow-row gap but says nothing about whether the relationship inverts at depth —against the impression the opening invites, as the argument is staged, given the stated qualifiers, on the evidence presented.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[True-But-Irrelevant] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."},{"id":"C","text":"At shallow depth, A recorded $23\\text{ g/kg}$ versus B''s $16\\text{ g/kg}$. A exceeds B at shallow depth, and since A also exceeds B at deep depth, only the shallow case fits while the inversion fails — so this supports the claim only where both rows are read together —against the impression the opening invites.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: its second sentence is the only one that satisfies the discriminating condition."},{"id":"D","text":"Method B''s storage declines from shallow to deep by $4\\text{ g/kg}$. This is an accurate within-method trend but does not compare A and B as the hypothesis requires —against the impression the opening invites, on the evidence presented, within the limits set out, as the text finally frames it.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Partial Match] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."}]'::jsonb, 'C', 'Logical Reconstruction:
